            <abstract encodinganalog="520" label="Abstract">Consists of photographs and
                correspondence describing the wartime experiences of Cheston Heath, organist and
                choirmaster at Christ Episcopal Church in Indianapolis, Indiana for twenty-one
                years. The collection also contains Xeroxed copies of two of Heath's original
                compositions.</abstract>
        </did>

